<paragraph id="8BE98519D116497679C3C6F7FBC533B5" blockId="15.[189,1086,1976,2003]" box="[189,1086,1976,2003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Baltic amber is considered to be of Bartonian–Priabonian age, ca 34–38 Ma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D109496979C3C047FEC230E9" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C047FEB53544" blockId="16.[189,334,264,290]" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
<heading id="D0A13275D109496979C3C047FEB53544" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496979C3C047FEB53544" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10949697994C078FEBE3537" blockId="16.[189,1399,311,619]" box="[234,325,311,337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697994C078FEBE3537" bold="true" box="[234,325,311,337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C014FBCF360D" blockId="16.[189,1399,311,619]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
BODY. BL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD1094969782FC015FE463513" box="[337,445,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.43" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="2.43">2.43 mm</quantity>
. Head smooth, bare (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697A74C015FC833513" box="[778,888,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.37">0.37 mm</quantity>
); eye round, small, less than a third of head length (ED = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697821C031FE3735FE" box="[351,460,382,408]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
); antenna bearing numerous short setae; toruli separated by shallow cleft; scape as long as pedicel and first three flagellomeres combined, at least as long as head; pedicel three times as long as wide; 13 flagellomeres; F1 two times as long as wide, narrower than pedicel; following flagellomeres gradually widening towards apex; F13 largest and longest of all (antennomeres length of 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD109496979C3C345FEDC3642" box="[189,295,522,548]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.46; P-0.16; F1-0.12; F2-0.08; F3-0.08; F4-0.08; F5-0.09; F6-0.08; F7-0.08; F8- 0.08; F9-0.08; F10-0.10; F11- 0.10; F12; 0.11; F13-0.19); mandibles simple, just crossing at tip; labial palpi three-segmented, first long, second narrowing at apex and third wider.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C3DCFC03373A" blockId="16.[189,1400,658,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
MESOSOMA. Shorter than metasoma (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697BBDC3DDFCC936CB" box="[707,818,658,685]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
); pronotum not elongate, epomia present; notauli deep and complete, convergent posteriorly; anterior scutellar pit suboval, wider than shortest distance between notauli; mesopleuron bare, with epicnemial pit and carina present; propodeum with plicae projecting posteriorly, forming teeth, median propodeal keel simple. Fore wing reduced, not reaching middle of propodeum (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697B58C250FD6E375F" box="[550,661,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.32">0.32 mm</quantity>
). Hind wing shorter (HwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697A90C250FBA7375F" box="[1006,1116,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.17">0.17 mm</quantity>
). Legs slender with few unorganized erect setae; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C2CBFE28304D" blockId="16.[188,1398,899,1067]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
METASOMA. Petiole cylindrical, slightly longer than wide (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697ADFC2CBFBF737F8" box="[929,1036,900,926]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697D19C2CBFB2837F8" box="[1127,1235,900,926]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.18">0.18 mm</quantity>
), with distinct longitudinal sculpture, and short hairs dorsally; gaster subcylindrical, elongate and tapering at apex (GL = 1.11; GH = ca 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD109496978C8C285FDD83782" box="[438,547,970,996]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
); T2 and S2 longest; T2 slightly striated dorsally at junction with petiole; T6 and T7 not clearly separated and forming long triangle; ovipositor exerted, slightly shorter than gaster (OL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10949697827C55FFE3C304D" box="[345,455,1040,1067]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.89">0.89 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10949697994C51DFED1300A" blockId="16.[189,313,1106,1167]" box="[234,298,1106,1132]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697994C51DFED1300A" bold="true" box="[234,298,1106,1132]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C53AFEC230E9" blockId="16.[189,313,1106,1167]" box="[189,313,1141,1167]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D109496979C3C5F9FCB832C6" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C5F9FEBF30B6" blockId="16.[189,324,1206,1232]" box="[189,324,1206,1232]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
<heading id="D0A13275D109496979C3C5F9FEBF30B6" bold="true" box="[189,324,1206,1232]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496979C3C5F9FEBF30B6" bold="true" box="[189,324,1206,1232]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C5AAFB1431C9" blockId="16.[188,1399,1253,1455]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10949697875C5AAFE443166" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[267,447,1253,1280]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697B7EC5AAFCFE3099" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[512,773,1253,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemyrevae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697B7EC5AAFCFE3099" box="[512,773,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Pantolyta chemyrevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10949697A73C5AAFC933099" box="[781,872,1253,1279]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697A82C5AAFAE93166" authority="Forster, 1856" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[1020,1298,1253,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697A82C5AAFB953099" box="[1020,1134,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Pantolyta</emphasis>
Förster, 1856
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: brachypterous, toruli rims without a distinct cleft, antennae 15-segmented, epomia on pronotum defined at pronotal collar, notauli present on mesoscutum, lower side of gaster slightly down curved. With the keys to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697A76C401FC81310E" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[776,890,1358,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697A76C401FC81310E" box="[776,890,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Pantolyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10949697D6EC401FA8D310F" author="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A." box="[1040,1398,1358,1385]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" pagination="163 - 176" refId="ref14352" refString="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A. 2019. Review of the Pantolyta genus (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae: Pantolytini) from Russia, with description of a new species. Zoosystematica Rossica 28: 163 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2019.28.1.163" type="journal article" year="2019">Chemyreva &amp; Kolyada (2019)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10949697990C43DFE7431EA" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[238,399,1393,1420]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon (1957)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD109496978E6C43DFDC431EA" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[408,575,1394,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemyrevae">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496978E6C43DFDC431EA" box="[408,575,1394,1420]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. chemyrevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys out near 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697B98C43DFC0831EA" authority="Kieffer, 1908" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[742,1011,1394,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylata">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697B98C43DFCAB31EA" box="[742,848,1394,1420]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. stylata</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1908
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697D67C43DFA9531EA" authority="sensu Nixon 1957" authorityName="Nixon" authorityYear="1957" box="[1049,1390,1393,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697D67C43DFB6F31EA" box="[1049,1172,1394,1420]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. vernalis</emphasis>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10949697D9CC43DFA9531EA" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[1250,1390,1393,1420]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) but has the antennal shelf less prominent and a longer scape (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10949697AF7C4DAFB1831C9" author="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A." box="[905,1251,1429,1455]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" pagination="163 - 176" refId="ref14352" refString="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A. 2019. Review of the Pantolyta genus (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae: Pantolytini) from Russia, with description of a new species. Zoosystematica Rossica 28: 163 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2019.28.1.163" type="journal article" year="2019">Chemyreva &amp; Kolyada 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D109496979C3C498FCB832C6" blockId="16.[188,1400,1494,1696]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
Among the Baltic amber species, it differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697A11C499FBBF3196" box="[879,1092,1494,1520]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697A11C499FC1A3196" box="[879,993,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Pantolyta</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
as follow: 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697DA7C498FAAD3196" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1999" box="[1241,1366,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697DA7C498FAAD3196" box="[1241,1366,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. antiqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is macropterous and has F1 more than two times as long as pedicel; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697AB5C4B6FB2F3275" baseAuthorityName="Buhl" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[971,1236,1529,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augustinusii">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697AB5C4B6FB2F3275" box="[971,1236,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">Pantolyta augustinusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the toruli separated by a distinct cleft, the mesoscutum bearing long hairs and the plicae not projecting posteriorly; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD109496979C2C70EFED4323C" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Buhl" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[188,303,1601,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janzeni">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496979C2C70EFED4323C" box="[188,303,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. janzeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697813C70EFDFA323C" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jouault &amp; Nel" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[365,513,1600,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perrichoti">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697813C70EFDFA323C" box="[365,513,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. perrichoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer petiole, more than two times as long as wide; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10949697DACC70EFA83323C" authorityName="Maneval" authorityYear="1938" box="[1234,1400,1600,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somnulenta">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10949697DACC70EFA83323C" box="[1234,1400,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. somnulenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD109496978EAC72BFDC5321B" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[404,574,1635,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemyrevae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496978EAC72BFDC5321B" box="[404,574,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. chemyrevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10949697B3BC72BFD593218" box="[581,674,1636,1662]" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but is macropterous, has anterior scutellar pit narrower than 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD109496979C1C7C8FE9C32C6" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[191,359,1670,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemyrevae">
<emphasis id="B922590BD109496979C1C7C8FE9C32C6" box="[191,359,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="73">P. chemyrevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the plicae less produced posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
